revision.text:
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Banishing Charm| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Charm)| features=Sends objects away from the caster| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Banishing Charms''''' are the opposite of [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Accio|Summoning Charms]], and are used to send an object away from the caster.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
Banishing charms are more difficult than summoning charms as you are not only impelling an object to move, but ideally you are also telling it where to move to. In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Filius Flitwick|Professor Flitwick]]'s class, we see that while nearly everyone has managed to send objects away from themselves (though in the case of [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Neville Longbottom|Neville]]'s efforts, sometimes it is the wrong object), only the best of the students is able to send their pillows unerringly into the box where they are intended to go.
We never hear the actual invocation of the banishing charm.
== Analysis ==
