{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Hand of Glory| type=Magical object| features=Allows the holder to see in darkness| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Chamber of Secrets|''Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets'']]}}
== Overview ==
The '''''Hand of Glory''''', a desiccated, severed human hand, is a candle holder; the person holding it is able to see in complete darkness by its candlelight, but to anyone else, the light is invisible.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
First seen at [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Borgin and Burkes|Borgin & Burkes]], a shop in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Knockturn Alley|Knockturn Alley]] dealing in Dark objects. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]], using [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Floo Powder|Floo Powder]] for the first time, accidentally lands in Borgin & Burke's. As he prepares to exit, he sees [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Draco Malfoy|Draco Malfoy]] and his father, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Lucius Malfoy|Lucius Malfoy]], entering the shop. Harry hides and overhears Borgin explaining the Hand of Glory and its function. It is, he says, a thief or plunderer's best friend; Lucius replies that he hopes Draco will be better than a thief or a plunderer...though unless his grades improve, that may be the best he can hope for.
Draco evidently does purchase a Hand of Glory, because [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ginny Weasley|Ginny]] sees him carrying it as he guides the Hogwarts invaders from the Room of Requirement; the hand apparently allows him to see where he is leading the Death Eaters despite the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Peruvian Instant Darkness Powder|Darkness Powder]] he tosses after spotting the D.A. members.
