{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Pepper-Up Potion| type=Potion| features=Restorative| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire/Chapter 26|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Pepper-Up Potion''''' is a restorative potion. It seems to have the side effect of making steam come out the drinker's ears.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
We first see this potion used after the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Second Task|Second Task]] of the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Triwizard Tournament|Triwizard Tournament]]. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Poppy Pomfrey|Madam Pomfrey]] is administering this potion to all of the Champions and their "treasures" (hostages to the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Merpeople|Merpeople]]) as they emerge from the lake. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] does indicate that he feels much warmer once the potion has been administered.
There is a Wizard candy, Pepper Imps, that apparently also makes steam come out the ears; likely it is based on this potion.
== Analysis ==
