== Overview ==
'''''Expulso''''' appears to be one of the many spells, like [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Confringo|Confringo]], that causes things to explode.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
We see the Expulso curse being used only once. Shortly after [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ron Weasley|Ron]], and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] leave [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Bill Weasley|Bill]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Fleur Delacour|Fleur]]'s wedding, they stop in an overnight café on the Tottenham Court Road. There, they are attacked by a pair of Death Eaters. One of the Death Eaters uses this spell to blow up the table behind Harry, who is hidden under his [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Invisibility Cloak|Invisibility Cloak]], possibly in an attempt to jinx Harry that misses.
== Analysis ==
While we believe this spell to be a simple explosive, it is uncertain; we have seen in previous battles that curses that miss their target seem to explode when they reach solid objects.
