When the family goes to visit [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Arthur Weasley|Arthur]] in the hospital for the first time after his injury, the adults there present, Arthur, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Molly Weasley|Molly Weasley]], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Alastor Moody|Mad-Eye Moody]], and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Nymphadora Tonks|Tonks]], send the youngsters out of the ward so they can have a quick discussion. Fred and George again produce Extendable Ears, saying that they hope nobody has thought to put an Imperturbable Charm on the door. It turns out nobody has.
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Half-Blood Prince/Chapter 6|''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince'']], when [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ron Weasley|Ron]], and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] have followed [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Draco Malfoy|Draco Malfoy]] to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Borgin and Burkes|Borgin and Burkes]], Ron produces Extendable Ears to allow them to listen in on what Draco is saying, and says that he hopes the store is not protected by an Imperturbable Charm.
