The author has nominated this book for speedy deletion, with this message: :''I am the original author with no other contributors (except for 1 vandal ;-)). I don't intend to finish this book as the material is not really useful. This book has not been put on any bookshelves either.'' I think this might be worth keeping, because it is a good start that somebody else might want to continue from. [[User:Webaware|Webaware]]&nbsp;<sup>[[User_talk:Webaware|talk]]</sup> 07:03, 13 February 2008 (UTC)
:{{keep}} - [[User:Webaware|Webaware]]&nbsp;<sup>[[User_talk:Webaware|talk]]</sup> 07:03, 13 February 2008 (UTC) :[[Image:Symbol comment vote.svg|15px]] '''{{{2|Comment}}}''' - I would love to keep this, as I noted on the author's talk page. But it ''does'' technically meet the speedy deletion criteria. On the other hand, there's nothing which forces any of us to actually delete it ;) and we would really be better off keeping it, so consider this a [[Image:Symbol keep vote.svg|15px]] '''{{{2|Keep}}}''' unless the author is highly unhappy about that. If they insist, then fine. &nbsp;'''&ndash;&nbsp;[[User:Mike.lifeguard|<font color="Indigo">Mike.lifeguard</font>]]'''&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;<sup>[[User talk:Mike.lifeguard|<font color="Indigo">talk</font>]]</sup> 13:33, 13 February 2008 (UTC) :{{keep}}, even if the author is made unhappy. I don't see a reason for him to be. --[[User:Panic2k4|Panic]] ([[User talk:Panic2k4|talk]]) 18:39, 17 February 2008 (UTC) |}

