== Swedish (Germanic) ==
*Swedish: ''svenska'' /{{IPA|'svɛnska}}/ *hello: ''hej'' /{{IPA|hɛj}}/ (hey) *good-bye: ''hej då'' /{{IPA|hɛj doː}}/ (HEY-doh) *please: ''tack'' /tak/ (tahck) as in “yes, please” or ''snälla'' /{{IPA|'snɛla}}/ (snella) as in “please, show me to the station” or “var så god” /{{IPA|vaʂɔ'guːd}}/ (vahr saw gohd) as in “please come in and make yourself at home” *excuse me: ''ursäkta mig'' /{{IPA|'ʉːʂɛkta mɛj}}/ or /{{IPA|ʉ'ʂɛkta mɛj}}/ (uor-SECKTAH may) *sorry: ''förlåt'' / (ferlawht) *thank you: ''tack'' /{{IPA|tak}}/ (tahck) *that one: ''den där'' /{{IPA|dɛn dæːɾ}}/ (den dehr) *how much?: ''hur mycket?'' /{{IPA|hʉːɾ 'mʏkːɛ}}/ (huwr MICK-eh) *English: ''engelska'' /{{IPA|'ɛŋːɛlska}}/ (ENG-el-skah) *yes: ''ja'' /{{IPA|jɑː}}/ or /{{IPA|ja}}/ (yah) *no: ''nej'' /{{IPA|nɛj}}/ (neiy) *generic toast: ''skål'' /{{IPA|skoːl}}/ (skal ''or'' skol) *banana: ''banan'' /{{IPA|ba'nɑːn}}/ (buh-NAAN) *what time is it?: ''vad är klockan?'' /{{IPA|vɑː æ 'klɔkːan}}/ (vaad air KLAWCK-an) *Where's the bathroom?: ''var är toaletten?'' /{{IPA|vɑːɾ æ tʊa'lɛtːɛn}}/ (vahr eyr twah-LET-en) *I don’t understand: ''jag förstår inte'' /{{IPA|ja fœ'ʂtoːɾ 'ɪntɛ}}/ (yah fur-SHTOHR in-teh) *Do you speak English?: ''Talar du engelska?'' /{{IPA|'tɑːlaɾ dʉ 'ɛŋːɛlska}}/ (TAH-lahr doo ENG-elska) [with NG as in 'siNGer', not as in 'fiNGer']
{{BookCat}}

== [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]/[[Filipino language|Filipino]] common phrases== '''Note:''' The more polite or formal forms of some phrases — those which make use of the word ''pô'' — should generally be used when speaking to persons of authority and seniority, or to show reverence to the person to whom spoken. With friends and in casual situations, ''pô'' need not be used. Also, in modern written Filipino/Tagalog, diacritical marks are not essential, and are omitted.
{| border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 |- bgcolor=#eeeeee ! align=left | Translation ! align=left | Phrase ! align=left | IPA ! align=left | Pronunciation |- valign=top |- | Tagalog || ''Tagalog'' || {{IPA|/tɐ"galog/}} || ''(ta-GA-log)'' |- | Filipino || ''Pilipino'' || {{IPA|/%pili"pino/}} || ''(pi-li-PI-no)'' |- | Hello/How are you? || ''Kumustá''/''Kumustá ka?'' || {{IPA|/kumus"ta (ka)/}} || ''(ku-mus-TAH (KA?))'' |- | I’m fine, and you? || ''Mabuti namán, ikáw?'' || {{IPA|/mɐ"butɛ nɐ"man, ʔi"kaʊ̯/}} || ''(ma-BU-ti na-MAN, iKAW?)'' |- | Good-bye || ''Paalam (pô)'' || {{IPA|/pɐ"ʔalam (poʔ)/}} || ''(pa-AH-lam (PO))'' |- | Please || ''pakí-''(verb) ''(pô)'' || {{IPA|/pɐ"ki (poʔ)/}} || ''(pah-KI (PO))'' |- | Thank you || ''Salamat (pô)'' || {{IPA|/sɐ"lamat (poʔ)/}} || ''(sa-LAH-mat (PO))'' |- | You're welcome || ''Waláng anumán (pô)'' (literally, “No problem”) || {{IPA|/ʊɐ"laŋ ʔɐnu"man (poʔ)/}} || ''(wa-LANG a-nu-MAN (PO))'' | |- | That one (object far from person spoken to) || ''Iyon (pô)'' [demonstrative] ''Ayun (pô)'' [reflective] || {{IPA|/ʔi"jon (poʔ)/}} || ''(i-YON (PO), a-YUN (PO))'' |- | That one (object near to/held by person spoken to) || ''Iyan (pô)'' [demonstrative] ''Ayan (pô)" [reflective] || {{IPA|/ʔi"jan (poʔ)/}} || ''(i-YAN (PO))'' |- | How much? || ''Magkano (pô)?'' || {{IPA|/mɐg"kano (poʔ)/}} || ''(mag-KAH-no (PO)?)'' |- | English language || ''wikang Ingglés'' || {{IPA|/ʔɪŋ"glɛs/}} || ''(ing-GLES)'' |- | Yes || ''Oo'' / ''Opò'' (polite form) || {{IPA|/"oʔo/, /"opoʔ/}} || ''(O-o) / (O-po)'' (all o's pronounced neutral) |- | No || ''Hindî '' || {{IPA|/hɪn"diʔ/, /hɪn"dɛʔ/}} || ''(hin-DI)'' or ''(hin-DE)'' |- | No (polite form) || ''Hindí pô'' || {{IPA|/hɪn"di (poʔ)/}} || ''(hin-DI PO)'' |- | Where's the bathroom? || ''Nasaán ang banyo?'' || {{IPA|/%nasɐʔan ʔaŋ "banjo/}} || ''(NA-sa-AN ang BAN-yoh?)'' |- | What is your name? || ''Anó ang pangalan mo?'' || {{IPA|/ʔɐ"no ʔaŋ pɐ"ŋalan mo/}} || ''(ah-NOH ang pa-NGA-lan MOH?)'' | |- | Sorry || ''Paumanhín (pô)'' || {{IPA|/pɐʔuman"hin (poʔ)/}} || ''(pa-u-man-HIN (PO))'' |- | I don’t know || ''Hindí ko (pô) alám'' || {{IPA|/hɪn"di ko (po) ʔa"lam/}} || ''(hin-DI ko (PO) a-LAM)'' |- | I don’t understand || ''Hindí ko (pô) naíintindihan'' || {{IPA|/hɪn"di ko (po) na"iɪntindihan/}} || ''(hin-DI ko (PO) na-I-in-tin-di-han)'' |- | Nakalimutan ko. || ''I forgot.'' || |- | Welcome/Generic toast || ''Mabuhay!'' (literally, “Long live!”) || {{IPA|/mɐ"buhaɪ/}} || ''(ma-BU-hai)'' |- | I am sick || ''Masamâ (pô) ang pakiramdám ko'' (literally, “I’m not feeling well”) || {{IPA|/masɐ"maʔ (po) ʔaŋ pɐkiɾɐm"dam ko/}} || ''(ma-sa-MAH po ang pa-ki-ram-DAM ko)'' |- | Do you speak English? || ''Marunong ka bang magsalitâ ng Ingglés?'' || {{IPA|/mɐ"runɔŋ ka baŋ mɐgsali"ta naŋ ʔɪŋ"glɛs/}} || ''(ma-ROO-nong ka BANG mag-sa-li-TA nang ing-GLES?)'' |}
[[Category:Tagalog]]

== Tamil (Dravidian) == Please note that spoken Tamil is very different from formal written Tamil.
The below phrases are in written Tamil and thus sound very awkward and stilted when used in everyday speech.
{| border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 |- bgcolor=#eeeeee ! align=left | Translation ! align=left | Phrase ! align=left | Pronunciation ! align=left | IPA |- valign=top
|- |Tamil |தமிழ் | |{{IPA|/t̪ɐmɨɹ/}} |- |hello |வணக்கம் |Vanakkam |{{IPA|/vəɳək:ɔ̃/}} |- |good-bye |சென்று வருகிறேன் |sentru varukireen |{{IPA|/sentu varukireen/}} |- |please |தயவு செய்து |thayavu seithu |{{IPA|/tajavu seiθu/}} |- |thank you |நன்றி |nandri |{{IPA|/nantʕi/}} |- |sorry |மன்னிக்கவும் |mannikkavum | |- |that one |அது |adhu |{{IPA|/əðɯ/}} |- |how much? |எவ்வளவு |evvalavu |{{IPA|/evːalavu/}} |- |yes |ஆம் |aam |{{IPA|/aːm/}} |- |no |இல்லை |illai |{{IPA|/ilːaj/}} |- |I don’t understand |எனக்குப் புரியவில்லை |ennaku puriyavillai | |- |Where's the bathroom? |குளியலறை எங்கே உள்ளது? |kuliyalarai engai ullathu? | |- |Hey!<ref>Generic toast only, not used in formal occasions and to elders.</ref> |டேய்! |dei |{{IPA|/de:i/}} |- |English |ஆங்கிலம் |aangilam |{{IPA|/aːŋilam/}} |- |Do you speak English? |நீங்கள் ஆங்கிலம் பேசுவீர்களா? |neengal aanglilam paysuveerkala? | |}
