==== strtod ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cstdlib>
double strtod( const char *start, char **end );
</source>
}}

The function strtod() returns whatever it encounters first in start as a double. end is set to point at whatever is left in start after that double. If overflow occurs, strtod() returns either '''HUGE_VAL''' or '''-HUGE_VAL'''.

<source lang=cpp>
x = atof( "42.0is_the_answer" ); 
</source>

results in x being set to 42.0.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/atof|atof]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== isalnum ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int isalnum( int ch );
</source>
}}

The function isalnum() returns non-zero if its argument is a numeric digit or a letter of the alphabet. Otherwise, zero is returned.

<source lang=cpp>
char c;
scanf( "%c", &c );
if( isalnum(c) )
  printf( "You entered the alphanumeric character %c\n", c ); 
</source>

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalpha|isalpha]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/iscntrl|iscntrl]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isdigit|isdigit]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isgraph|isgraph]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isprint|isprint]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ispunct|ispunct]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isspace|isspace]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isxdigit|isxdigit]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== isalpha ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int isalpha( int ch );
</source>
}}

The function isalpha() returns non-zero if its argument is a letter of the alphabet. Otherwise, zero is returned.

<source lang=cpp>
char c;
scanf( "%c", &c );
if( isalpha(c) )
  printf( "You entered a letter of the alphabet\n" );    
</source>

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalnum|isalnum]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/iscntrl|iscntrl]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isdigit|isdigit]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isgraph|isgraph]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isprint|isprint]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ispunct|ispunct]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isspace|isspace]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isxdigit|isxdigit]]

