==== iscntrl ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int iscntrl( int ch );
</source>
}}

The iscntrl() function returns non-zero if its argument is a control character (between 0 and 0x1F or equal to 0x7F). Otherwise, zero is returned.

