==== isprint ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int isprint( int ch );
</source>
}}

The function isprint() returns non-zero if its argument is a printable character (including a space). Otherwise, zero is returned.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalnum|isalnum]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalpha|isalpha]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/iscntrl|iscntrl]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isdigit|isdigit]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isgraph|isgraph]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ispunct|ispunct]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isspace|isspace]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== ispunct ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int ispunct( int ch );
</source>
}}

The ispunct() function returns non-zero if its argument is a printing character but neither alphanumeric nor a space. Otherwise, zero is returned.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalnum|isalnum]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalpha|isalpha]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/iscntrl|iscntrl]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isdigit|isdigit]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isgraph|isgraph]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isspace|isspace]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isxdigit|isxdigit]]

