==== isspace ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int isspace( int ch );
</source>
}}

The isspace() function returns non-zero if its argument is some sort of space (i.e. single space, tab, vertical tab, form feed, carriage return, or newline). Otherwise, zero is returned.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalnum|isalnum]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isalpha|isalpha]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/iscntrl|iscntrl]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isdigit|isdigit]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isgraph|isgraph]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isprint|isprint]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ispunct|ispunct]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/isxdigit|isxdigit]]

