==== isxdigit ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cctype>
int isxdigit( int ch );
</source>
}}

The function isxdigit() returns non-zero if its argument is a hexadecimal digit (i.e. A-F, a-f, or 0-9). Otherwise, zero is returned.

